[1] Cholera - Cuba (Granma Province)
Data: Mon 31 Aug 2015
Source: Cubanet [machine trans. edited]
https://www.cubanet.org/noticias/detectan-nuevos-casos-de-colera-en-granma/


During the weekend of (29-30 Aug 2015), 11 cases of cholera were detected in the Granma Province town of Niquero. Those affected were admitted to the Calana Gerardo Hospital, where they are receiving care.

Sources belonging to the municipal health sector, who have not wanted to give their names for fear of reprisals, confirmed the cases and that they have been reported to the Provincial Health Directorate. They also revealed that they have received orientation to stay alert to the emergence of new cases to intensify epidemiological work.

Dr. Haydee Sanchez Pupo, provincial director of health at the province, refused to give information about what is happening. He confirmed that this eastern province is on alert and ready to face any possible epidemic.

Dr. Junior Aguilar Garcia said he was not authorized to provide information to the independent press.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
http://www.promedmail.org/

[The outbreak of cholera in Cuba was 1st reported in the eastern province of Granma in July 2012 (Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update 2012 (23): Cuba (GR) RFI Archive Number: 20120702.1187070), and, subsequently, cases spread to the western part of the island to include the Greater Havana area. The origin of the outbreak strain was thought to be from Cuban medical personnel who traveled to Haiti to help in the outbreak there.

2 earlier cases of cholera were acquired in Cuba in travelers returning to Italy and the UK during 2015 (Public Health Agency of Canada: Travel Health Notice: Cholera in Cuba, Dominican Republic, Haiti and Mexico. Updated 20 Mar 2015; http://phac-aspc.gc.ca/tmp-pmv/notices-avis/notices-avis-eng.php?id=111; Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (24): Americas 20150703.3480336). These were not reported from Cuba to PAHO. - Mod.LL]

