[4] Cholera - South Sudan (Central Equatoria State)
Date: Tue 1 Sep 2015
Source: Radio Tamazuj [edited]
https://radiotamazuj.org/en/article/68-new-south-sudan-cholera-cases-last-week-1-death


There have been 68 new cholera cases in South Sudan in the last week and one death, according to the UN's Office for Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs. This is a slight dip from the previous week, when 88 new cases were reported.

South Sudan has had 1675 total cholera cases including 46 deaths as of 28 Aug 2015, representing a case fatality rate of 2.75 percent, OCHA said in a press release. This is up from 1607 cases including 45 deaths at the end of the previous week. Cholera cases in 2015's outbreak have been reported in Juba, Bor, and Pibor since June 2015. [But the report above says "As of 16 Aug 2015, a total of 1600 cholera cases including 45 deaths (CFR 2.8 percent)". - Mod.JW]

During a cholera outbreak last year [2014], there were 6421 cases including 167 deaths in South Sudan, representing a case fatality rate of 2.6 percent.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The cholera situation in Haiti remains at least an order of magnitude worse than any of these outbreaks. - Mod.LL

The outbreak in Haiti has been ongoing since October 2010 -- 10 months after the catastrophic earthquake. So far, nearly 9000 people have died, and more than 730 000 have been infected -- see ProMED archive Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (22): Africa, Haiti: 20150604.3407655 -- nearly as many deaths as from Ebola in West vAfrica. - Mod.JW

